article.description: Daniel Giddens and Ryan Davis scored 17 points apiece as Vermont romped past Division III Gallaudet University 93-44 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Vermont tops Gallaudet University 93-44
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Daniel Giddens and Ryan Davis scored 17 points apiece as Vermont romped past Division III Gallaudet University 93-44 on Wednesday night. Stef Smith added 14 points for the Catamounts, while Duncan Demuth and Eric Beckett each had 10. Davis also had 10 rebounds. Noah Valencia had 11 points and five rebounds for the Bison. Steve Valencia-Biskupiak added three assists. Preston Kelly had six assists. Vermont (6-2) matches up against Yale on the road on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
